arted \r\n[DEBUG  ] ReaderThread(<_io.FileIO name=19 mode='rb' closefd=True>, <queue.Queue object at 0x7fcffc556610>, ['git', 'annex', 'version', '--raw']) exiting (stream end) \r\n[DEBUG  ] ReaderThread(<_io.FileIO name=16 mode='rb' closefd=True>, <queue.Queue object at 0x7fcffc556610>, ['git', 'annex', 'version', '--raw']) exiting (stream end) \r\n[DEBUG  ] Process 221500 exited with return code 0 \r\n```\r\n\r\nI assume that this can be decoded to two thread being used to capture the output of the command. However, when thing work at the level of basic IO, but debugging is needed at a higher level (i.e. what is conceptually happening in a flow of command executionS) this verbosity, all at the same level, is a big distraction and makes things hard to read.\r\n\r\nEither the self-description of the threads should be optimized/shortened, or their log level is demoted, or both.\r\n\r\n@christian-monch WDYT?", "closed_by": {"login": "mih", "id": 136479, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjEzNjQ3OQ==", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/136479?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih", "html_url": "https://github.com/mih", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/datalad/datalad/issues/5772/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocke